    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="412"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.11 Se 8/40½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-09">9 <hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >August</hi>, 1915</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I approve of this note, though
                    I must say that I do so with a little hesitation.</p>
                <p>My hesitation is due to the very thing Mr. Anderson points out in his memorandum:
                    that the principle of arbitration may be a little too acceptable to the German
                    Government and may lead to the proposal from them that the matter of the <hi
                        rend="italic">Lusitania</hi> also be so submitted, and I do not think that
                    public opinion in this country will stand for that at present.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
